[src:locality-sensitive-hashing/locality-sensitive-hashing] The algorithm then constructs L hash tables, each corresponding to a different randomly chosen hash function g.
[src:locality-sensitive-hashing/locality-sensitive-hashing] In the preprocessing step we hash all n d-dimensional points from the data set S into each of the L hash tables.
[src:locality-sensitive-hashing/locality-sensitive-hashing] Given that the resulting hash tables have only n non-zero entries, one can reduce the amount of memory used per each hash table to $O(n)$ using standard hash functions.
[src:locality-sensitive-hashing/locality-sensitive-hashing] Given a query point q, the algorithm iterates over the L hash functions g.
